**Timeline of computing** presents events in the history of computing
 organized by year and grouped into six topic areas: predictions and concepts,
 first use and inventions, hardware systems and processors, operating systems,
 programming languages, and new application areas.

**Detailed computing timelines**: [before 1950](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_2400_BC-1949 "Timeline of computing 2400 BC-1949"), [1950–1979](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_1950%E2%80%931979 "Timeline of computing 1950–1979"), [1980–1989](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_1980%E2%80%931989 "Timeline of computing 1980–1989"), [1990–1999](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_1990%E2%80%931999 "Timeline of computing 1990–1999"), [2000–2009](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_2000%E2%80%932009 "Timeline of computing 2000–2009"), [2010–2019](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_2010%E2%80%932019 "Timeline of computing 2010–2019"), [2020–present](/wiki/Timeline_of_computing_2020%E2%80%93present "Timeline of computing 2020–present")

